    thinking: "**Designing CustomerHome.tsx**\n\nI\'m making excellent progress on the `CustomerHome.tsx` component. I\'m focusing on the core elements. First, the hero offer banner is in place, and I\'m deciding whether to use a claim button or a different interactive method for the discount. Then, the category slider is next. I\'m excited about including the recently ordered section with reorder buttons!\n\n\n**Developing Restaurant Features**\n\nI\'ve been exploring the reorder functionality \342\200\223 clicking \"Reorder\" should add the item directly to the cart, ideally opening the cart view or showing a success message. I\'m excited about the restaurant section, where users can filter, sort (by rating, distance, time), and view restaurant menus. I\'m leaning toward creating an interactive menu drawer within `CustomerHome.tsx` to display meal options, customizations, and add-to-cart functionality. I\'m reviewing screenshots to craft descriptions and structure the component beautifully.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/CustomerHome.tsx` which contains:\n1. An immersive, interactive hero banner to claim coupons.\n2. A responsive category carousel with slide controls.\n3. A \"Recently Ordered\" section with action-oriented \"Reorder\" binds.\n4. \"Top Rated Restaurants\" grid with interactive search filtering, active categories, sorting (by rating, time, or distance), and status filters (like Free Delivery).\n5. A beautifully designed \"Restaurant Menu Modal\" that pops open when any restaurant is selected. It mimics a high-performance bottom sheet, enabling users to choose item customizations and add items to their Cart."
