  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Celebrating Initial Success**\n\nI\'m thrilled! The applet compiled flawlessly on the first attempt; a very satisfying result. I\'m now double-checking for cleanup items, like stray files or variables. The Vite config is spot-on, no packages are missing. I did not remove anything.\n\n\n**Verifying Image Referrers**\n\nI\'ve meticulously reviewed the code for image tags. Every instance of an `<img>` tag now correctly includes `referrerPolicy=\"no-referrer\"`, as requested. I double checked the `CustomerHome.tsx`, `CartScreen.tsx` and `OrderTracking.tsx` files. I\'m pleased with the consistency. I am now proceeding with the next stage of the review.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have built the **ZyropFoodOrder** prototype application using React, Vite, and Tailwind CSS. The app features a highly coherent **Modern Corporate** aesthetic with a friendly, food service-oriented visual style:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Aesthetic Design\n- **Color & Depth**: Anchored in a vibrant \"Safety Orange\" primary flavor (`#a83300`) to stimulate appetite and capture attention, contrasting with neutral architectural grays and a warm off-white surface tone (`#fbf9f8`). Built with soft ambient shadows to convey depth and layered tactile containers.\n- **Approachable Shapes**: Generous `rounded-2xl` cushioning on cards, food drawers, and search capsules that make elements feel responsive and touch-friendly.\n- **Premium Typography**: Features the **Plus Jakarta Sans** typeface for sharp legibility on mobile and desktop viewports, with distinct typographic weights for headings and micro-copy.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\223\262 Immersive Screen Workflow\n\n#### 1. Discovery Home Dashboard (`CustomerHome`)\n- **Category Carousel**: An interactive horizontal carousel to explore cuisines like Pizza, Burgers, Sushi, and Drinks, complete with tactile swipe controls.\n- **Claimable Promotions**: Implements an active deal banner where claiming a *50% Off* voucher applies live discounts across checkouts.\n- **Recently Ordered Section**: Fully active cards featuring quick `\"Reorder\"` actions that immediately queue items into the Cart with notification feedback.\n- **Sort & Filter Suite**: Flexible sorting controls to dynamically rank restaurants by highest customer rating, delivery speed, or geographical proximity.\n- **Restaurant Menu Modal**: Clicking on any partner (like *The Steakhouse Grill* or *Pasta Fresca*) reveals an interactive bottom menu slide-up. Users can read ingredients, toggle custom toppings, and add items to their Cart.\n\n#### 2. Basket Checkout Card (`CartScreen`)\n- **Quantity Anchors**: Allows customers to review items, edit counts, and remove selections seamlessly.\n- **Interactive Payments**: Support for Stripe secure credit cards or fast UPI checkout options.\n- **Simultaneous Fee Aggregation**: Dynamic cost summary calculations including base subtotals, restaurant delivery fees, taxes, and active discount coupon subtractions.\n\n#### 3. Live Order Tracking (`OrderTracking`)\n- **Interactive Street Map**: A custom logistics map utilizing styled coordinates pinning the customer drop-off point, the kitchen, and the moving delivery agent.\n- **Live Simulator Engine**: Features a prototype simulation panel. Clicking **\"Run Simulation\"** triggers a real-time tracking time-lapse. Watch rider Marcus Rodriguez move across streets, while estimated arrival minutes run down, and milestones dynamically register as completed.\n- **Interactive Chat & Call Overlays**: Complete with a realistic messaging dialog. Customers can type directives and receive back automated status updates from the driver. Triggering **\"Call Marcus\"** launches a calling state layer.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 2
      nanos: 671972523
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
